----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
###***To communicate with ESP32,firstly install the necessary USB-->UART Driver for operating System***### 
-----*After successful installation,the ESP32 will show as a Communication Port under Device Manager*-----
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
### If you want to programming your ESP32 using Python scripts;

--->Use any IDE(Integrated Development Environment) like:
1. Thonny
2. Visual Studio Code (VS Code) with PlatformIO
3. PyCharm
4. uPyCraft IDE
5. MikroPython IDE (MikroPython Tool)
6. Eclipse with PyDev
--->Burn the necessary firmware for ESP32 dev Board to run Python scripts Using IDE.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
